      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_trainee",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Training steps</h3><b>Objective:</b>There is a relationship between our fingers and the symbols we use to count. In this step as a trainee, your mission is to complete the counting sequence using different models. This training will help reinforce your knowledge.</p><p><b>Rules:</b> Select a way to represent the counting. Half of the values will be preloaded, and you will complete the other half using the arrows on the side (<i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-up upArrowWithFA\" style=\"font-size: 1.5em\" name=\"traineeUp\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-down downArrowWithFA\" style=\"font-size: 1.5em\" name=\"traineeDown\"></i>). When you finish, you can restart the training by clicking the \"Start again\" button.</p><p>Couting model: <input type=\"radio\" value=\"ha\" name=\"selModel\" /> <b><span id=\"firstMethod\"></span></b> <input type=\"radio\" value=\"indigenous\" name=\"selModel\" /> <b><span id=\"secondMethod\"></span></b> <input id=\"playButton\" type=\"button\" /></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><table id=\"yupana0\" class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th colspan=\"4\">Translate the second line using arrows on side (<i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-up upArrowWithFA\" style=\"font-size: 1.5em\" name=\"traineeUp\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-down downArrowWithFA\" style=\"font-size: 1.5em\" name=\"traineeDown\"></i>).</th><th>Increase</th><th>Decrease</th></tr> <tr id=\"tf1\"><td id=\"tc1f1\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc2f1\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc3f1\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc4f1\">&nbsp;</td><td id=\"tc5f1\" rowspan=\"3\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-up upArrowWithFA\" name=\"traineeUp\"></i> </td><td id=\"tc6f1\" rowspan=\"3\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-caret-down downArrowWithFA\" name=\"traineeDown\"></i></td></tr> <tr id=\"tf2\"><td id=\"tc1f2\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc2f2\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc3f2\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc4f2\">&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr><td colspan=\"4\"><span id=\"gameMessage\"></span></td></tr> </table>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            }
         ]
      },
      {
         "id": "SECTION_game",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><h3>Discovering America (<i>Abya Ayala</i>)</h3><b>Objective and rules:</b>Our objective is to translate the indigenous numerations that will appear, either on <i>Yupana</i> format or in the Mesoamerican format. With each value you translate, you will learn about an indigenous region in America (<i>Abya Ayala</i>). You can advance to the next mission by clicking on <i class=\"fa-solid fa-play\" style=\"color: Tomato;\"></i>. At the end, you will receive a medal (<i class=\"fa-solid fa-medal\" style=\"color:gold;\"></i>) for your work.</p><p><b>Note:</b> To read a number on the Yupana, we must look at all four squares. In contrast, Mesoamerican numbers are represented in a single square.</p><p><table id=\"yupana1\" class=\"tawapukllay\"><tr><th colspan=\"4\">Translate the first line and discover indigenous constructions.</th></tr> <tr id=\"tf1\"><td id=\"tc1f1\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc2f1\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc3f1\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc4f1\">&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr id=\"tf2\"><td id=\"tc1f2\">&nbsp;</div></td> <td id=\"tc2f2\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc3f2\">&nbsp;</td> <td id=\"tc4f2\">&nbsp;</td></tr> <tr id=\"tf3\"><td colspan=\"3\" id=\"tc1f3\"><span id=\"gameImage\"></span></td><td id=\"tc4f3\"><div id=\"descImage\"></div> <span style=\"font-size: 3em; color: Tomato;\"><i id=\"nextLevel\" class=\"fa-solid fa-play\"></i></span></td></tr> </table>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p class=\"desc\">We work with <i>Yupana</i> using the <i>\"Yupana Inka Tawa Pukllay\"</i> method, developed and published by Dhavit Prem (<htcite0>) of the Yupanki Association (<htcite1>).<br />The use of Mesoamerican numbers is based on the work of Orlando Josué Casares Contreras, José M. Gamboa Cetina y Venus Sarahí Estrella Cabrera (<htcite2> ; <htcite3>). Additionally, we incorporate the work of Francisco Barriga Puente, and Ximena Catepillán (<htcite4> ; <htcite5>).<br /> Finally, we utilize various counting methods inspired by the work of Francisco A. González Redondo <i>et al.</i> (<htcite6>).</p>",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "2d2ea4a5-506b-4dbf-aaa4-3a10a8fbbd9c",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit",
                     "page": "",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "07",
                        "day": "25"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a62b520a-f443-4d83-ab51-b99c9a46dab8",
                     "text": "Prem, Dhavit",
                     "page": "",
